    <stitle>7 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER PS110-7, PS145-7 - DISASSEMBLE - SHIFTER HOUSING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="8">
        <title>SHIFTER HOUSING</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1301604">Figure 4</hotlnk>
            and
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1301605">Figure 5</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1301604" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1301604" filename="../figg13/G1301604.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 4. Shifter Housing Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1301605" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1301605" filename="../figg13/G1301605.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 5. Center Control Shifter Housing Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the bolts and separate the shifter housing from the transmission case. Place the
                shifter housing on a bench with the forks up and in the neutral position (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301606">Figure 6</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301606" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301606" filename="../figg13/G1301606.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 6. Place Shifter Housing on Bench With Forks Up</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the oil trough (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301607">Figure 7</hotlnk>). This will make disassembling the rest of the shifter
                housing easier.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301607" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301607" filename="../figg13/G1301607.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7. Remove Oil Trough</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen all fork and bracket setscrews, then remove the retainer straps (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301608">Figure 8</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301608" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301608" filename="../figg13/G1301608.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 8. Remove Retainer Straps</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">All forks lift easily from the shifter housing. Remove the interlocks, poppets, and springs
                (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301609">Figure 9</hotlnk>). The 1st-reverse spring has a different tension than the
                others; avoid mixing them up during reassembly. If you do, shifting problems could result.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301609" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301609" filename="../figg13/G1301609.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9. Remove Interlocks, Poppets, and Springs</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disassemble the forks and brackets (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301610">Figure 10</hotlnk>). Inspect all parts for wear or damage. Replace if
                necessary.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301610" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301610" filename="../figg13/G1301610.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 10. Disassemble Forks and Brackets</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the poppet and detent holes for burrs or damage (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301611">Figure 11</hotlnk>). If either exists, replace the cover.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301611" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301611" filename="../figg13/G1301611.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 11. Inspect Poppet and Detent Holes</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
